<span id="freeTextContainer2833051407182929352">To say &quot;I really liked it&quot; is not accurate; but I am so very glad that I read this book (huge thank you to Dave Cullen for the recommendation). <br/><br/>Ms. Klebold is honest and reflective in ways that I cannot imagine. It seems to me that she genuinely only bared her life and soul with the earnest hope that someone can learn from her &quot;mistakes&quot;. Much of her story is scarier than Stephen King, but hers is a horror we can learn from and hopefully avoid in our own lives. <br/><br/>I admire the courage, diligence &amp; </span>
  <span id="freeText2833051407182929352" style="display:none">To say "I really liked it" is not accurate; but I am so very glad that I read this book (huge thank you to Dave Cullen for the recommendation). <br /><br />Ms. Klebold is honest and reflective in ways that I cannot imagine. It seems to me that she genuinely only bared her life and soul with the earnest hope that someone can learn from her "mistakes". Much of her story is scarier than Stephen King, but hers is a horror we can learn from and hopefully avoid in our own lives. <br /><br />I admire the courage, diligence &amp; tenacity that went into every single sentence in this book and I appreciate the knowledge I've gained.</span>
